==English==

===Etymology===
The name was coined by Charles de Brosses in ''Histoire des navigations aux terres australes'' 1756. He derived it from the {{L.}} for “south of [[Asia]]”

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪʒə|-eɪʒə]]

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Australasia'''

# [[Australia]], [[New Zealand]], [[New Guinea]] and neighbouring [[island]]s
# all of [[Oceania]]

====Usage notes====
This is an ambiguous term, whose precise meaning varies considerably depending on its field of use

